# Money Tracker Pro

A modern personal finance desktop app built with PySide6 (Qt) and SQLite. Track income/expenses, manage savings goals with automatic allocations, export monthly data, preview charts, and optionally email monthly reports.

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.9+-blue.svg)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-purple.svg)

## Features
- Balance tracking with income/expense entries
- Savings goals with:
  - Allocation percentages (auto-funding on income)
  - Progress bars, deadlines, and completion notifications
- Monthly allowance auto-apply
- Reporting:
  - Export current month to CSV
  - Preview monthly balance chart (PNG via Matplotlib)
  - Email monthly report (with optional auto-send on startup)
- Dark, minimal UI

## Screenshots
- Balance card, goal cards, reports toolbar (export/preview/email/settings)
- Chart: balance trend for the current month

## Tech Stack
- Python 3.9+
- PySide6 (Qt for Python)
- SQLite3 (built-in)
- Matplotlib
- smtplib/email (built-in)

## Installation
1. Clone the repo:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/F0xyN0xy/expense_tracker.git
   cd expense_tracker
   ```

Copy

Insert

Install dependencies:
pip install PySide6 matplotlib

Copy

Insert

(sqlite3, smtplib, and email ship with Python.)
Usage
Run the app:

python MoneyTrackerApp.py

Copy

Insert

Add Money / − Spend Money: create transactions
Savings Goals:
Add Goal: name, target, allocation %, deadline, optional initial funding
Total allocations across goals must be ≤ 100%
Reports:
Export Month: writes finance_YYYY_MM.csv
Preview Chart: saves balance_YYYY_MM.png
Send Report: emails current month summary and chart
Settings: configure SMTP and auto-send
Email Setup
Open Reports → Settings and provide:

SMTP server/port and SSL toggle
Sender email and app password
Recipient email
Auto-send monthly report on startup (optional)
Note: Use an app password (e.g., Gmail App Password) rather than your main email password.

Data Storage
SQLite database file: finance.db
Tables: transactions, goals, allowance, app_settings
Automatic migrations for goals schema when needed
Security
Email credentials are stored in the local database. Protect your machine and database file.
Consider environment-based secrets for production use.
